results.definition: a state of ill-being due to affliction or misfortune
examples: the misery and wretchedness of those slums is intolerable

results.definition: the character of being uncomfortable and unpleasant
examples: the wretchedness for which these prisons became known
the grey wretchedness of the rain

results.definition: the quality of being poor and inferior and sorry
examples: he has compiled a record second to none in its wretchedness
